WEBVTT

00:04.750 --> 00:07.420
♪ Magic is real here ♪

00:07.500 --> 00:10.090
♪ Far away from home ♪

00:10.170 --> 00:12.420
♪ Anything can happen ♪

00:12.510 --> 00:15.430
♪ When witches make the rules ♪

00:15.510 --> 00:17.760
♪ Monsters are cool ♪

00:17.850 --> 00:20.810
♪ The moon is our friend ♪

00:20.890 --> 00:23.100
♪ I wanna stay with you ♪

00:23.180 --> 00:26.980
♪ On Summer Camp Island ♪

00:28.860 --> 00:35.860
♪♪

00:35.950 --> 00:38.700
Great.
So now Mildred is immortal too.

00:38.780 --> 00:39.870
Wait a minute there.

00:39.950 --> 00:42.370
Too?
You're immortal?

00:42.450 --> 00:43.710
Oh, yeah.

00:43.790 --> 00:45.620
I forgot
to mention that.

00:45.710 --> 00:48.630
Oh, you two are going
to drive me crazy.

00:48.710 --> 00:50.130
First things first.

00:50.210 --> 00:51.590
Go find her.

00:51.670 --> 00:53.300
I'm not an expert
on immortality,

00:53.380 --> 00:57.680
but it's probably not wise to
start out forever with a grudge.

00:57.760 --> 00:59.760
I think
an apology is in order.

00:59.850 --> 01:02.640
If she wants to apologize,
she knows where to find me.

01:02.720 --> 01:03.770
No.

01:03.850 --> 01:06.140
I meant you apologize
to Mildred.

01:06.230 --> 01:08.060
What? No way.
Not this time.

01:08.150 --> 01:09.310
I'm gonna wait right here.

01:09.400 --> 01:12.150
Mildred can come to me
when she's ready.

01:12.230 --> 01:14.490
It's not my fault.

01:14.570 --> 01:18.070
Why does everybody think
everything is my fault?

01:18.660 --> 01:19.990
Ah!

01:20.070 --> 01:21.200
Aah!

01:21.280 --> 01:24.660
Oi, you better compose yourself,
young lady.

01:24.750 --> 01:29.000
Ugh! I am composed.

01:29.080 --> 01:31.040
Aah!

01:33.800 --> 01:36.800
Witch! Witch!
Run!

01:36.880 --> 01:39.510
-Don't let her get you.
-That one over there.

01:39.590 --> 01:41.300
She's a witch!

01:41.390 --> 01:42.850
[ Indistinct shouting ]

01:42.930 --> 01:45.230
♪♪

01:45.310 --> 01:46.560
Ugh.

01:46.640 --> 01:55.690
♪♪

01:55.780 --> 01:59.780
Well, I guess I need
something to sulk on.

01:59.860 --> 02:01.910
Hmph.

02:01.990 --> 02:03.740
What are we doing?

02:03.830 --> 02:08.160
We're waiting for Susie
to come apologize.

02:08.250 --> 02:09.540
Who's Susie?

02:09.620 --> 02:10.710
She's my sister.

02:10.790 --> 02:12.710
She said some
really mean stuff to me

02:12.790 --> 02:16.630
and it made me have a tantrum
and made me run away.

02:16.710 --> 02:18.220
Actually...

02:18.300 --> 02:21.390
she's probably getting pretty
worried about me right now.

02:21.470 --> 02:24.220
Wondering where I am.

02:24.310 --> 02:26.890
You know what,
you'll meet her in a second.

02:26.980 --> 02:29.520
She's going to be looking
for me all over.

02:29.600 --> 02:32.560
Great. I can't wait for you
to introduce us.

02:32.650 --> 02:36.110
Uh, what did you say
your name was again?

02:36.190 --> 02:37.240
My name?

02:37.320 --> 02:38.570
I'm not sure.

02:38.650 --> 02:40.450
What's your name?
Mildred.

02:40.530 --> 02:42.910
Oh.
I'm Mildred's Friend.

02:42.990 --> 02:44.080
Easy enough.

02:44.160 --> 02:46.410
Now we wait.

02:46.490 --> 02:48.580
[ Sighs ]

02:48.660 --> 02:50.670
Hey, when did you say
Susie was coming?

02:50.750 --> 02:52.130
I don't have any plans.

02:52.210 --> 02:54.710
But I-I do have
anxiety.

02:54.790 --> 02:56.960
Oh.
We didn't set a time.

02:57.050 --> 03:00.300
I'm just kind of basing it off
her past find-me-times.

03:00.380 --> 03:01.430
Okay.

03:01.510 --> 03:03.600
I'll try to lower
my expectations.

03:03.680 --> 03:04.930
So...

03:05.010 --> 03:08.640
do you think this is going to be
an all-night thing?

03:08.730 --> 03:10.730
Should we set up camp?

03:10.810 --> 03:12.730
Camp! Yeah.

03:12.810 --> 03:14.770
Do you know
what we do first?

03:14.860 --> 03:17.230
Uh, no.

03:17.320 --> 03:21.650
Well, Susie usually does
the main stuff.

03:21.740 --> 03:23.320
I do the extras.

03:23.410 --> 03:24.780
The fun parts.

03:24.870 --> 03:27.450
But I guess
I could try.

03:30.200 --> 03:31.870
Hey,
I did it.

03:31.960 --> 03:33.960
[ Frogs croak ]

03:34.040 --> 03:36.790
Hmph.

03:36.880 --> 03:38.590
How about this?

03:40.670 --> 03:41.970
Oh.
Thanks.

03:42.050 --> 03:44.800
I-I guess this works.

03:44.890 --> 03:47.680
Susie will be here
in the morning anyways.

03:51.600 --> 03:53.100
Ugh,
don't look at me like that.

03:53.190 --> 03:56.230
I liked you better
when you were a brooch.

03:56.310 --> 03:57.520
Okay, fine.

03:57.610 --> 03:59.320
I'll go physically put myself
in front of her

03:59.400 --> 04:01.860
so she can
apologize to me.

04:01.950 --> 04:04.160
-Tell us where the witch is.
-She mixed up all our parts.

04:04.240 --> 04:06.030
Man: I can't look at corn
the same way again.

04:06.120 --> 04:07.530
-Bring us the witch!
-We want justice!

04:07.620 --> 04:08.830
We want justice!

04:08.910 --> 04:11.500
If we find out you're hiding
that little witch --

04:11.580 --> 04:13.670
[ Sighs ]
Miss Mary?

04:13.750 --> 04:16.500
Susie, this city is looking
for Mildred.

04:16.580 --> 04:19.710
If anyone asks, don't tell them
you're her sister.

04:19.800 --> 04:22.340
Some people are really mad
at her right now.

04:22.420 --> 04:25.340
But Mildred is out there.
All alone.

04:25.430 --> 04:28.680
Mildred's fine.
You know she can hold her own.

04:28.760 --> 04:29.850
Come on.

04:29.930 --> 04:31.640
Let's go back to bed.

04:31.720 --> 04:34.600
Susie, promise me
you won't go out there.

04:34.690 --> 04:36.190
Promise.

04:36.270 --> 04:42.190
♪♪

04:42.280 --> 04:43.190
Weird.

04:43.280 --> 04:44.860
Your sister
didn't show up.

04:44.950 --> 04:47.320
Yeah.
I noticed.

04:47.410 --> 04:48.320
You know what?

04:48.410 --> 04:49.780
Who needs Susie?

04:49.870 --> 04:51.370
I'll make a new Susie,

04:51.450 --> 04:53.790
and then I won't need
old Susie.

04:53.870 --> 04:54.910
Great.

04:55.000 --> 04:58.040
Lousy Susie,
always being so mean to me.

04:58.130 --> 05:00.090
That'll show old Susie.

05:02.960 --> 05:04.050
Hup.

05:04.130 --> 05:06.970
[ Coughing ]

05:07.050 --> 05:08.890
What am I?

05:08.970 --> 05:11.430
You're my sister,
New Susie.

05:11.510 --> 05:13.430
I'm in pain.

05:13.520 --> 05:17.230
Maybe try moving around
a little, you know, walk it off?

05:17.310 --> 05:19.520
[ Groaning ]

05:19.610 --> 05:21.440
Can I do
something else?

05:21.520 --> 05:23.400
Sit down?

05:25.320 --> 05:26.990
Hmm. Ah. Aah!

05:27.070 --> 05:28.570
Like this?

05:28.660 --> 05:31.910
Uh, you're nothing
like Susie.

05:31.990 --> 05:34.450
Ah-ha.
This should do the trick.

05:36.710 --> 05:37.870
This is all your fault!

05:37.960 --> 05:39.920
You're always
ruining everything!

05:40.000 --> 05:41.630
Our parents left
because of you!

05:41.710 --> 05:43.090
Ugh!

05:43.170 --> 05:44.420
So this is the end?

05:44.510 --> 05:45.590
Life was just...

05:45.670 --> 05:47.010
an accumulation of...

05:47.090 --> 05:50.140
disappointments.

05:50.220 --> 05:51.600
What are we doing?

05:51.680 --> 05:53.430
[ Gasps ]

05:53.510 --> 05:55.600
Are you being bad?

05:55.680 --> 05:57.100
What? No.

05:57.190 --> 05:58.440
You are.

05:58.520 --> 05:59.810
Okay, well...

05:59.900 --> 06:04.110
sometimes you have to be bad
to be good?

06:04.190 --> 06:05.820
Look,
if you keep quiet,

06:05.900 --> 06:08.650
you can have all
my figgy pudding for a month.

06:08.740 --> 06:09.950
A year.

06:10.030 --> 06:12.580
Great, sure. A year, whatever.
Bye now. Shh.

06:14.950 --> 06:17.460
[ Whisper shouting ]
Mildred!

06:17.540 --> 06:18.790
Mildred!

06:18.870 --> 06:20.790
Mildred, Mildred,
Mildred, Mildred.

06:20.880 --> 06:22.790
Mildred!

06:22.880 --> 06:24.420
Mildr--
Oh, my goodness.

06:24.500 --> 06:25.920
Look at this mess.

06:26.010 --> 06:28.630
Have you by any chance seen
a little girl with blue hair?

06:28.720 --> 06:30.260
Bold commitment
to the unibrow?

06:30.340 --> 06:32.640
Oh, you must be on
the search committee.

06:32.720 --> 06:34.600
Please,
take some flyers.

06:34.680 --> 06:36.140
My kids made them.

06:36.220 --> 06:37.310
Oh, no.

06:37.390 --> 06:39.600
Hey, I thought
they were pretty good.

06:39.690 --> 06:40.980
-There!
-Aah!

06:41.060 --> 06:42.310
That's her sister.

06:42.400 --> 06:44.820
Yeah.
The hot corn twins.

06:44.900 --> 06:46.480
-Of course. Twins.
-Same eyebrow.

06:46.570 --> 06:47.940
We are not twins.

06:48.030 --> 06:49.650
I was two long years
in this world without her.

06:49.740 --> 06:52.820
Capture one hot corn twin,
capture them both.

06:52.910 --> 06:55.990
-Susie?
-Miss Mary!

06:56.080 --> 06:57.370
Get them!

06:57.450 --> 06:59.370
-Get her!
-Bring her in!

07:01.330 --> 07:03.210
[ Sighs ]

07:03.290 --> 07:05.840
When you existentially exhale
like that,

07:05.920 --> 07:10.420
it makes me want to cry,
so please don't.

07:10.510 --> 07:12.220
Ta-da.
Check it out.

07:12.300 --> 07:14.140
I'm Susie now.
[ Laughs ]

07:14.220 --> 07:16.680
Whatever you want to dish at
her, you can dish at me.

07:16.760 --> 07:19.430
No,
I want her to dish at me.

07:19.520 --> 07:21.690
I'm not a mind reader.

07:21.770 --> 07:24.360
Just, uh,
tell me what to say.

07:24.440 --> 07:25.860
You're supposed to say,

07:25.940 --> 07:28.690
"Oh, Mildred, I'm so sorry
for yelling at you

07:28.780 --> 07:31.490
after you opened
my special box in my room

07:31.570 --> 07:34.660
that I've been hiding and
cherishing for my whole life,

07:34.740 --> 07:38.410
and then accidentally turned
my very special witch brooch

07:38.490 --> 07:40.580
into a frog."

07:40.660 --> 07:42.330
Like that.

07:42.420 --> 07:43.710
Yeah, yeah.

07:43.790 --> 07:45.590
There's no way
I'm gonna remember all of that.

07:45.670 --> 07:49.710
Behold as I capture
her essence with improv.

07:49.800 --> 07:51.550
I'm Susie and I'm bad.

07:51.630 --> 07:53.720
I'm sorry, Mildred,
for getting mad at you

07:53.800 --> 07:56.390
when you messed up
my special necklace

07:56.470 --> 08:00.140
and robbed me
of my birthday joy.

08:00.220 --> 08:04.400
Oh, Susie, I didn't mean
to mess up your birthday.

08:04.480 --> 08:06.360
I was just trying to make up
for earlier

08:06.440 --> 08:09.730
when I embarrassed you
in front of those mean girls.

08:09.820 --> 08:12.780
Okay, yeah,
I messed up some stuff.

08:12.860 --> 08:14.950
I always mess stuff up.

08:15.030 --> 08:17.160
I probably should've
listened to you,

08:17.240 --> 08:19.240
been a pinch more reserved.

08:19.330 --> 08:21.250
I'm sorry, Susie.

08:21.330 --> 08:24.790
I am a great actress.

08:24.870 --> 08:26.670
I'm going to
apologize to her,

08:26.750 --> 08:30.170
then we'll go to the Frozen
North to find Mum and Pop.

08:30.250 --> 08:32.510
Wait.
What is that flyer?

08:32.590 --> 08:33.970
What's it say, Mildred?

08:34.050 --> 08:36.090
It says I'm a criminal.

08:36.180 --> 08:38.680
It says
I should be locked up.

08:38.760 --> 08:41.430
Uh-oh.
My anxiety is back.

08:41.520 --> 08:43.850
It's okay.
We can still go find Susie.

08:43.940 --> 08:46.560
We just can't be seen.
Oh, that's perfect.

08:46.650 --> 08:48.940
I turn invisible
when I'm anxious.

08:49.020 --> 08:52.070
Look at that.

08:52.150 --> 08:53.950
Townspeople:
Bad witch, bad witch,

08:54.030 --> 08:56.450
find and bind the bad witch.

08:56.530 --> 08:58.030
You'll apologize
to these people

08:58.120 --> 09:00.410
after you apologize
to Susie, yeah?

09:00.490 --> 09:02.950
I'm not sure
that would help.

09:03.040 --> 09:04.290
Susie?

09:04.370 --> 09:06.290
Susie, where are you?

09:06.370 --> 09:07.830
Susie!

09:07.920 --> 09:11.960
She's not here.
Have you seen my sister?

09:12.050 --> 09:13.010
Answer me.

09:13.090 --> 09:15.800
I was told to "quiet down,"
so no,

09:15.880 --> 09:18.800
I'm not sure
I have anything to say.

09:18.890 --> 09:20.470
Alright, alright.

09:20.550 --> 09:23.270
Susie packed up her trunk
and left in a hurry.

09:23.350 --> 09:25.850
What?
That's all I know, I swear.

09:25.940 --> 09:28.100
Please,
make me beautiful again.

09:28.190 --> 09:32.480
I'm sorry.
I don't know how.

09:32.570 --> 09:34.490
Susie's gone.

09:34.570 --> 09:37.820
She's gone.
I have no one.

09:37.910 --> 09:39.280
You have me.

09:39.370 --> 09:41.370
Would you go to the Frozen North
with me?

09:41.450 --> 09:43.370
We'll find Mum
and Pop there.

09:43.450 --> 09:45.500
They'll know what to do.

09:45.580 --> 09:48.330
Parents love me.

09:48.420 --> 09:50.210
Townspeople:
Find and bind the bad witch.

09:50.290 --> 09:52.550
Find and bind the bad witch.

09:54.420 --> 09:56.170
Where am I going,
Miss Mary?

09:56.260 --> 09:57.680
You're off to America.

09:57.760 --> 09:59.340
It'll be a fresh start.

09:59.430 --> 10:01.350
Will you send Mildred my way
when you find her?

10:01.430 --> 10:05.180
Oh, don't worry.

10:05.270 --> 10:06.730
Well, here we are.

10:06.810 --> 10:08.190
Let's have a look at you.

10:08.270 --> 10:09.350
I'll miss you, Susie.

10:09.440 --> 10:12.360
You were my best
selling hot corn girl.

10:12.440 --> 10:14.150
I'll miss you too.

10:14.230 --> 10:16.860
Three times the figgy
for me.

10:16.940 --> 10:18.320
Yeah,
goodbye, Rachel.

10:18.400 --> 10:19.530
Off you go now.

10:19.610 --> 10:21.450
Eat your vitamin C.

10:21.530 --> 10:23.740
Don't talk to any
third-wave pilgrims.

10:23.830 --> 10:25.370
Bon voyage.

10:25.450 --> 10:33.250
♪♪

10:35.300 --> 10:39.130
♪♪

10:39.220 --> 10:41.470
[ Groans ]
Can't sleep either?

10:41.550 --> 10:43.510
I'm a third-wave pilgrim.
We all are.

10:43.600 --> 10:45.600
This is a ship full
of third-wave pilgrims.

10:45.680 --> 10:47.890
Are you running from
that bad, bad, bad witch?

10:47.980 --> 10:49.390
I hope that
in the new world,

10:49.480 --> 10:51.400
witches pay for
what they did to my baby.

10:51.480 --> 10:53.230
But excuse me,
that was a lot.

10:53.310 --> 10:54.480
Here's some anti-witch
literature.

10:54.570 --> 10:56.690
Perhaps
it will help you sleep.

10:58.650 --> 10:59.740
[ Crying ]

10:59.820 --> 11:01.740
Don't talk to me
until we get there.

11:01.820 --> 11:04.870
♪♪

11:06.700 --> 11:12.420
♪♪

11:12.500 --> 11:18.090
♪♪

11:18.170 --> 11:20.880
Three times the figgy for me.
